The paper proposes a model for personalized POI recommendation using contextual information, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The model is based on recurrent neural networks (RNN) and its variants, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The evaluation of the proposed model involves analyzing real-world data sets, which could fall under social networks (cs.SI) or data mining (cs.DM) sub-categories, but these are less likely than the other categories mentioned.
